name: Sue Semrau
biography: Susan Paige Semrau is the former head women's basketball coach at Florida State University. From 1997 through 2022, Semrau compiled a 468-252 career record at FSU. She retired after her 24th season at FSU. During the 2020–21 season she took a leave of absence to care for her mother. She guided the Seminoles to appearances in the NCAA tournament 15 total times, including 14 out of the past 15 seasons including three Elite Eights. Until her final season, Semrau at FSU never lost a 1st Round NCAA tournament game, going 15-0. In the 2019–20 season, she hit the 200 ACC wins milestone as a head coach.

name: Adrian Grenier
biography: Adrian Sean Grenier is an American actor. He is best known for his portrayal of Vincent Chase in the television series Entourage (2004–2011). He has appeared in films such as Drive Me Crazy (1999), The Devil Wears Prada (2006), Trash Fire (2016), and Marauders (2016). In 2021, he acted in the Netflix series Clickbait.

name: Evelyn Farkas
biography: Evelyn Nicolette Farkas is an American national security advisor, author, and foreign policy analyst. She is the current executive director of the McCain Institute, a nonprofit focused on democracy, human rights, and character-driven leadership.

name: Evgenia Belyakova
biography: Evgeniya Alexandrovna Belyakova is a Russian professional basketball player. A professional since 2004, Belyakova plays for Russia women's national basketball team and competed in the 2012 Summer Olympics and three EuroBasket Women.

name: Chantel Tremitiere
biography: Chantel Ruth Tremitiere is an American former professional women's basketball player.

name: Kim Perrot
biography: Kim Perrot was an American basketball player. She played in the WNBA for the Houston Comets and won three championships, the third being a posthumous honor by the Comets.

name: Tiffany Woosley
biography: Tiffany Woosley is a former professional basketball player. In her senior year at University of Tennessee she injured her right knee, sidelining her for the rest of the season. She coached at Lincoln County High School in Fayetteville, Tennessee in the 1996–97 school year before beginning her WNBA career. She currently lives in Shelbyville though previously lived in Tullahoma.

name: Yolanda Moore
biography: Yolanda Moore is an American former professional basketball player. She was the post game radio analyst for the Memphis Grizzlies in 2007.

name: Travis Trice
biography: Travis Lamar Trice II is an American professional basketball player for the Beijing Royal Fighters of the Chinese Basketball Association (CBA). He played college basketball for the Michigan State Spartans, leading his team in points during the 2014–15 NCAA Division I men's basketball season. He attended Wayne High School in Huber Heights, Ohio, where he played under his father, Travis Trice Sr.

name: Chrissy Roberts
biography: Chrissie Roberts is an American college basketball coach and the former women's head coach at Eastern Kentucky University (EKU) in Richmond, Kentucky.

name: Larry Joe Inman
biography: Larry Joe Inman is an American college basketball coach. The Tennessee State Lady Tigers are members of the Ohio Valley Conference (OVC) and compete in the NCAA's Division I. In 1991, while at Eastern Kentucky, Inman became the first coach to earn the OVC Coach of the Year award at two different schools, having previously been so honored at Middle Tennessee.

name: Irina Sokolovskaya
biography: Irina Borisovna Sokolovskaya is a Russian basketball player. She was part of the Russian national team that won the bronze medal at the 2008 Olympics. She plays for Dynamo Moscow in the Russian Premier League.

name: Patrick Aquino
biography: Patrick Henry Aquino is a Filipino basketball coach who serves as the head coach of the Philippines women's national basketball team, he has been appointed by the Samahang Basketbol ng Pilipinas since December 2014 when the team have a new corporate backer Ever Bilena, replacing long-time mentor Haydee Ong. This is the second time that Aquino has coached a national team, Aquino was once manned coaching duties for the Philippines women's national under-19 basketball team. Among his coaching achievements for promoted into Level 1 of 2017 FIBA Asia Women's Championship.

name: Armel Traoré
biography: Armel Traoré is a French professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association (NBA), on a two-way contract with the South Bay Lakers of the NBA G League. He plays the small forward position.

name: Austin Reaves
biography: Austin Tyler Reaves is an American professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He played college basketball for the Wichita State Shockers and the Oklahoma Sooners. He joined the Lakers as an undrafted free agent.

name: Bob Beyer
biography: Robert C. Beyer is an American professional basketball coach who is as an assistant coach for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association (NBA).

name: Conner Henry
biography: Conner David Henry is an American professional basketball coach and former player who is an assistant coach for the Charlotte 49ers men's basketball team. He played collegiately for the UC Santa Barbara Gauchos, and was selected by the Houston Rockets, with the 89th overall pick of the 1986 NBA draft. Henry had short stints with four National Basketball Association (NBA) teams, in two seasons, before he embarked on a career in the American minor leagues and overseas.

name: Jaxson Hayes
biography: Jaxson Reed Hayes is an American professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He played college basketball for the Texas Longhorns.

name: Martin Schiller
biography: Martin Schiller is an Austrian professional basketball coach who is currently serving as head coach of Rasta Vechta of the German Basketball Bundesliga (BBL).

name: Quincy Olivari
biography: Quincy Andrew Olivari is an American professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association (NBA), on a two-way contract with the South Bay Lakers of the NBA G League. He played college basketball for the Rice Owls and the Xavier Musketeers.

name: Ronnie Burrell
biography: Ronnie Burrell is an American former professional basketball player who is an assistant coach for the Portland Trail Blazers.

name: Aaron Gate
biography: Aaron Gate is a New Zealand road and track cyclist, who currently rides for UCI ProTeam Burgos BH. He represented his country in track cycling at the 2012, 2016 and 2020 Summer Olympics. Gate is the first New Zealand athlete to win four gold medals at a single Commonwealth Games.

name: Abbie Palmer
biography: Abbie Palmer is a New Zealand professional squash player. Her highest ranking was number 83 in the world in June 2018.

name: Aidan Sarikaya
biography: Aidan Thomas Sarikaya is a New Zealand field hockey player who plays as a defender or midfielder for Belgian club Herakles and the New Zealand national team.

name: Naile İvegin
biography: Naile İvegin Çırak is a Turkish female basketball player. The 1.85 m national plays power forward. She currently plays for Antalya 07 Basketbol SK.

name: Olga Arteshina
biography: Olga Dmitrievna Arteshina is a Russian basketball player. Since 2000 she played in most international competitions for the Russian national team, except for the 2008 Olympics which she missed due to giving birth to a daughter; she won an Olympic bronze medal in 2004 and three gold and four silver medals at the world and European championships. At the club level she was the EuroLeague champion in 2005, 2013 and 2016.

name: Silvia Dominguez
biography: Silvia Domínguez Fernández is a Spanish basketball player for Perfumerías Avenida and the Spain women's national basketball team. She won three EuroLeague Women and multiple medals for Spain.

name: Tatiana Popova (basketball)
biography: Tatiana Popova is a Russian professional basketball player. She plays for Russia women's national basketball team. She competed in the 2012 Summer Olympics.

name: Tuğçe Canıtez
biography: Tuğçe Canıtez is a Turkish retired female professional basketball player. The 1.90 m tall athlete plays in the power forward position.

name: Yasemin Begüm Dalgalar
biography:
Yasemin Begüm Dalgalar is a Turkish female basketball player for Adana ASKİ in the Power forward position.
She is 1.85 m tall and 70 kg (150 lb) weight.
